body.plain: Devon originally revealed part of ‘Suburbia’ to her TikTok audience in April 2021, and, having achieved close to two million views on the video, released the full song on the 23rd of July.

annotations: I have to leave, he’s on his way
These lines suggest the secret and illicit nature of the relationship between the narrator and the girl she sings about. The girl’s boyfriend is coming home, so the narrator has to leave their house.
Paint the walls with pink and orange
“Pink and orange” may be a reference to the lesbian flag:

Black and white is boring
 He goes down on you, you’re snoring

The girl that the narrator sings about has a boyfriend, but he is dull — so dull that she is falling asleep during sex.

“Black and white” might be a reference to a theoretical ‘straight flag,’ as usually such a flag is illustrated as just a bunch of black and white stripes.
